'''''Microworld''''' is a 1981 [[text adventure]] published by [[Med Systems Software]] for the [[TRS-80]]. An [[Atari 8-bit computer]] version followed.<ref name="mania">{{cite web |title=Microworld |url=http://www.atarimania.com/game-atari-400-800-xl-xe-microworld_7186.html |website=Atari Mania}}</ref>

==Gameplay==
''Microworld'' is a text only adventure game in which the player becomes an "electroid" and searches inside the circuits of a [[TRS-80]] computer for colored [[integrated circuit]] chips.<ref name="SG"/>

==Reception==
Allen L. Wold reviewed ''Microworld'' in ''[[The Space Gamer]]'' No. 52.<ref name="SG">{{cite journal|last=Wold |first=Allen L.|date=June 1982 |title=Capsule Reviews|journal=[[The Space Gamer]]|publisher=[[Steve Jackson Games]]|issue=52|pages=40}}</ref> Wold commented that "for the intelligent child, the adventure gaming beginner, or someone who'd just like to 'get into' his or her computer for a while, ''Microworld'' can be a lot of fun."<ref name="SG"/>

